A Google Workspace Admin manages Google’s enterprise collaboration platform for organizations, including:
Core services you administer

Gmail (mail routing, security, spam, compliance)
Google Drive (storage, sharing, DLP)
Google Calendar
Google Meet
Google Docs / Sheets / Slides
User & group management
Security policies & access controls
Identity & SSO with third‑party apps

Daily responsibilities

Creating/deleting users
Email migrations (Exchange → Gmail)
Managing groups, aliases, routing rules
Security hardening (2FA, DLP, context‑aware access)
Troubleshooting mail delivery and access issues
Supporting audits & compliance holds

👉 In short: GWS Admin = collaboration + identity + security admin


